"Honey**
    Hello, I am ** from Ingnok after-sales service department.
Judging from the video/pictures you provided, it is caused by the limited number of ports on your device that can transmit video signal sources.

Theory: One port can only output one video signal, and one video signal corresponds to one external monitor.
To put it simply, assuming your notebook has 2 Type-c3.1 ports and 1 HDMI port, the connection method is as follows:
Among them, one type-c3.1 port is connected to an external monitor, using TYPE-C video signal;
You can also connect the second type-c3.1 port to an external monitor (you need to power the monitor at the same time, because connecting multiple monitors at the same time will cause insufficient power supply to the device)
The last HDMI port is also connected to an external monitor and must power the monitor at the same time because the HDMI port does not have a power supply function.

If the number of monitors you connect exceeds the number of ports, there will be no signal for monitors without signal source inputs due to insufficient signal sources. Hope this helps.
    If you encounter any questions later while using the monitor, please feel free to contact us.
    Looking forward to hearing from you.
    Best regards!"		"亲爱的**
   您好，我是来自Ingnok售后服务部门的**。
从您提供的视频/图片来看，由于您的设备能够传输视频信号源的端口数量有限所导致的。

理论：一个端口只能输出一个视频信号，一个视频信号对应一台外接显示器。
简单来说，假设您的笔记本有2个Type-c3.1端口，1个HDMI端口，连接方式如下：
其中，1个type-c3.1端口连接一台外接显示器，使用的是TYPE-C的视频信号；
第2个type-c3.1端口您也将其与外接显示器连接，（需要同时为显示器供电，因为同时连接多台显示器会导致设备供电功率不足）
最后一个HDMI端口也与外接显示器连接，必须同时为显示器供电，因为HDMI端口没有供电功能。

如果您连接的显示器数量超过了端口的数量，会因为信号源数量不足，导致没有信号源输入的显示器没有信号。希望这能够帮到您。
   如果之后在使用显示器的过程中遇到任何疑问，请随时与我们联系。
   期待您的回信。
   此致敬意！"
